W.R. Grace and Co said it completedthe sale of its Bermans The Leather Experts retail business toa new company in a management led buyout.    Grace received 99.3 mln dlrs cash and will record a pretaxgain of about 37 mln dlrs in the first quarter, the companysaid. An additional pretax gain of 19 mln dlrs will be deferreduntil realization is more fully assured, it said.    The diversified chemical and industrial company said thesale completes its program to divest retail operations.    In addition to the cash payment, Grace received warrants tobuy up to 47.5 pct of the new company and has reinvested about19 pct of the proceeds in debt of the new firm.    Financing was provided by Prudential Insurance Co ofAmerica and affiliates. Reuter&#3;